1
20:00:00,938 --> 20:00:02,385
Don't move.

2
20:00:03,801 --> 20:00:05,975
- This is my mate, Justin.
- Hey there.

3
20:00:05,991 --> 20:00:07,279
- Hey.
- And I love him.

4
20:00:07,280 --> 20:00:09,642
All I want is what you want.

5
20:00:09,658 --> 20:00:11,011
To have these people locked up,

6
20:00:11,042 --> 20:00:12,911
so they can't do any more harm

7
20:00:13,031 --> 20:00:13,928
to anyone else.

8
20:00:13,928 --> 20:00:16,094
Justin, I think I may
have taken a wrong turn.

9
20:00:16,214 --> 20:00:17,323
Do you want to talk about this properly?

10
20:00:17,362 --> 20:00:19,810
- That's why I'm here.
- No, I mean, properly.

11
20:00:19,820 --> 20:00:22,171
I'm not sure what's
supposed to be going on here.

12
20:00:23,140 --> 20:00:24,666
I'm completely lost.

13
20:00:24,713 --> 20:00:25,886
That's why we're here.

14
20:00:25,894 --> 20:00:29,695
To help you understand
how lost you really are.

15
20:00:30,180 --> 20:00:33,699
How am I supposed to trust
you if you don't trust me?

16
20:00:34,100 --> 20:00:35,580
I will be back.

17
20:00:36,580 --> 20:00:39,019
I'm a copper, we're on the same side.

18
20:00:39,020 --> 20:00:40,276
I don't think you're going to shoot me.

19
20:00:40,613 --> 20:00:42,552
I warned you not to make me your enemy!

20
20:00:42,672 --> 20:00:45,876
- I warned you!
- No. Don't you... don't you...

21
20:00:45,907 --> 20:00:48,180
Hey. Get up!

22
20:01:00,055 --> 20:01:01,940
Justin.

23
20:02:18,604 --> 20:02:20,860
Please.

24
20:02:42,626 --> 20:02:44,778
Oh, God. Key. Key. Key.

25
20:05:09,380 --> 20:05:11,705
Are you ok? You ok?

26
20:05:14,940 --> 20:05:16,580
Mary.

27
20:05:19,220 --> 20:05:21,384
What did John say to you exactly?

28
20:05:22,179 --> 20:05:24,856
He said... he said he was busy.

29
20:05:25,260 --> 20:05:28,020
And that I should meet
him here, at his place.

30
20:05:36,700 --> 20:05:37,551
No.

31
20:05:44,740 --> 20:05:46,086
Erin?

32
20:05:48,500 --> 20:05:50,020
Man down.

33
20:05:51,420 --> 20:05:53,060
Justin Ripley.

34
20:06:19,085 --> 20:06:21,619
So what is it with John Luther

35
20:06:22,345 --> 20:06:24,359
and the people he loves?

36
20:06:47,380 --> 20:06:49,430
John, I don't know what to say.

37
20:06:49,874 --> 20:06:51,395
I don't have the words.

38
20:07:02,900 --> 20:07:05,134
Where is Mary?

39
20:07:07,180 --> 20:07:08,731
John Luther,

40
20:07:09,300 --> 20:07:13,355
you're under arrest for the murder
of Detective Sergeant Justin Ripley

41
20:07:13,980 --> 20:07:16,702
and the attempted murder of Mary Day.

42
20:07:32,224 --> 20:07:34,821
Mary! Hey, Mary. Mary!

43
20:07:35,334 --> 20:07:36,579
Hold on!

44
20:08:48,244 --> 20:08:49,289
Ok.

45
20:08:49,546 --> 20:08:52,411
From this side of the table, it looks like

46
20:08:52,993 --> 20:08:55,477
there's two people who
could incriminate you,

47
20:08:56,420 --> 20:08:58,679
one of which is now dead

48
20:08:58,917 --> 20:09:01,670
by the hand of Tom Marwood.

49
20:09:01,860 --> 20:09:05,361
And Mary Day would be...
had I not intervened.

50
20:09:05,481 --> 20:09:08,208
And you're welcome, by the way.

51
20:09:10,620 --> 20:09:13,500
You told her where to go, John.

52
20:09:15,940 --> 20:09:17,537
You told her where

53
20:09:18,681 --> 20:09:19,720
and when.

54
20:09:20,903 --> 20:09:24,250
And I think you did that
because you wanted Marwood

55
20:09:24,920 --> 20:09:26,628
to kill her for you.

56
20:09:30,860 --> 20:09:32,021
Yesterday,

57
20:09:32,090 --> 20:09:35,456
a few hours before he shot
and killed Justin Ripley,

58
20:09:35,481 --> 20:09:37,615
you spoke for some time to Mr Marwood.

59
20:09:37,900 --> 20:09:40,600
Your report notes that
during this conversation,

60
20:09:40,618 --> 20:09:43,420
Tom Marwood asked for more time.

61
20:09:45,274 --> 20:09:47,540
"Give me two days."

62
20:09:50,573 --> 20:09:52,081
And then you let him go.

63
20:09:54,180 --> 20:09:57,093
Which makes me wonder,
what was the quid pro quo?

64
20:09:57,140 --> 20:09:58,269
Shut your mouth.

65
20:09:58,306 --> 20:10:00,108
You let Marwood

66
20:10:00,822 --> 20:10:04,995
run free to kill his paedophiles and his

67
20:10:05,195 --> 20:10:07,104
scumbags.

68
20:10:09,220 --> 20:10:11,076
That's no skin off your nose.

69
20:10:11,107 --> 20:10:12,715
No humans involved.

70
20:10:12,778 --> 20:10:14,504
But then in exchange,

71
20:10:14,554 --> 20:10:16,000
does you a favour.

72
20:10:18,460 --> 20:10:20,700
He cleans up your mess.

73
20:10:30,215 --> 20:10:31,415
I loved him.

74
20:10:56,980 --> 20:10:58,879
He's got too many friends.

75
20:10:59,085 --> 20:11:00,706
We'll have to move him.

76
20:11:33,333 --> 20:11:34,659
What is this, John?

77
20:11:35,066 --> 20:11:36,618
I don't know, George.

78
20:11:37,037 --> 20:11:38,532
Stay here.

79
20:12:09,100 --> 20:12:10,519
Erin!

80
20:12:26,818 --> 20:12:28,540
Wotcher.

81
20:12:31,300 --> 20:12:35,457
'Detective Ripley has been hailed
a hero by his colleagues after

82
20:12:35,500 --> 20:12:39,029
'he was shot point blank in the
chest by vigilante Thomas Marwood

83
20:12:39,035 --> 20:12:41,113
'who has been branded a coward... '

84
20:13:01,180 --> 20:13:02,424
Oh.

85
20:13:03,275 --> 20:13:05,503
If you're going to go on the
run you're going to have to, er,

86
20:13:05,503 --> 20:13:07,092
lose the coat.

87
20:13:07,820 --> 20:13:09,407
It's my lucky coat.

88
20:13:10,020 --> 20:13:11,383
Lucky?!

89
20:13:11,878 --> 20:13:14,224
Right. Well, I would take it
back to the shop, if I was you.

90
20:13:14,620 --> 20:13:16,946
Get your money back.
It's obviously defective.

91
20:13:26,300 --> 20:13:27,662
This is a nice place.

92
20:13:28,300 --> 20:13:29,939
Is it yours?

93
20:13:29,940 --> 20:13:31,700
Don't be silly.

94
20:13:32,611 --> 20:13:34,075
Alice, what are you doing here?

95
20:13:34,500 --> 20:13:35,780
I saw the news.

96
20:13:36,647 --> 20:13:37,873
Where have you been?

97
20:13:38,300 --> 20:13:39,462
Berlin.

98
20:13:39,860 --> 20:13:40,994
I don't believe you.

99
20:13:41,580 --> 20:13:43,300
Oh, you should.

100
20:13:52,180 --> 20:13:54,316
I assumed you'd need it, eventually.

101
20:13:54,940 --> 20:13:56,620
Not yet.

102
20:13:58,195 --> 20:13:59,759
After Marwood.

103
20:14:00,404 --> 20:14:01,880
Then I'm done.

104
20:14:01,918 --> 20:14:04,220
Why? Because he killed your puppy?

105
20:14:06,100 --> 20:14:07,786
Oh, that's why you're here?

106
20:14:08,962 --> 20:14:10,589
To rub my nose in it?

107
20:14:10,860 --> 20:14:11,908
No.

108
20:14:13,466 --> 20:14:15,606
I came to help the people you love.

109
20:14:15,919 --> 20:14:16,744
I'm sorry?

110
20:14:16,794 --> 20:14:19,272
You assert this fabulous
moral conscience, John.

111
20:14:20,022 --> 20:14:23,019
This adherence to unwritten
law. Yet, time and again,

112
20:14:23,301 --> 20:14:27,300
it devastates the people you claim
to hold dear, but you don't stop.

113
20:14:28,326 --> 20:14:32,342
It seems to me your conscience
has killed more people than I have.

114
20:14:55,420 --> 20:14:58,251
Well, you know, you say "escape," George,

115
20:14:58,288 --> 20:15:01,980
but to me, this looks more like
the scene of a violent abduction.

116
20:15:04,220 --> 20:15:05,665
By Marwood?

117
20:15:06,380 --> 20:15:07,341
Presumably.

118
20:15:07,366 --> 20:15:08,812
Why not pop him here?

119
20:15:09,756 --> 20:15:11,133
The way he did Ripley?

120
20:15:11,176 --> 20:15:13,942
Well, we won't know that
until we ask him, will we?

121
20:15:13,967 --> 20:15:15,244
In the meantime,

122
20:15:15,287 --> 20:15:16,708
somewhere out there,

123
20:15:16,733 --> 20:15:18,297
there is a police officer

124
20:15:18,417 --> 20:15:20,637
in the hands of a known police killer.

125
20:15:20,656 --> 20:15:22,464
Well, either way, Martin...

126
20:15:23,009 --> 20:15:25,180
we both want DCI Luther

127
20:15:25,211 --> 20:15:26,444
returned to us

128
20:15:26,675 --> 20:15:28,357
at the earliest opportunity.

129
20:15:28,352 --> 20:15:30,404
A search is under way.

130
20:15:30,417 --> 20:15:31,881
Then widen it.

131
20:15:34,064 --> 20:15:35,090
You know, George,

132
20:15:35,128 --> 20:15:38,412
the Tom Marwood investigation
is under my command,

133
20:15:38,600 --> 20:15:40,052
and God help you

134
20:15:40,060 --> 20:15:41,309
if you interfere with it

135
20:15:41,429 --> 20:15:43,668
or question my allocation of resources.

136
20:15:44,362 --> 20:15:47,040
DCI Luther does have some loyal friends,

137
20:15:47,221 --> 20:15:49,540
- doesn't he?
- Oh, yes, he does.

138
20:15:54,620 --> 20:15:58,229
'One officer was shot dead
and another badly injured.

139
20:15:58,500 --> 20:16:01,728
'In what the police say
may be a related incident,

140
20:16:01,778 --> 20:16:05,019
'Milan Knizac has been
attacked in Mortlake Prison.

141
20:16:05,340 --> 20:16:07,299
'Knizac is serving a life sentence

142
20:16:07,300 --> 20:16:11,169
'for the murder of Caitlin
Marwood, Tom Marwood's late wife.

143
20:16:11,420 --> 20:16:14,499
'Caitlin Marwood was raped
and murdered by Milan Knizac

144
20:16:14,500 --> 20:16:17,512
'four years ago, after he
was released from prison

145
20:16:17,540 --> 20:16:20,100
'less than halfway through
a nine-year sentence... '

146
20:16:22,486 --> 20:16:24,629
- What do you want?
- Don't move!

147
20:16:40,959 --> 20:16:42,854
So where are we going?

148
20:16:42,873 --> 20:16:44,738
We're taking you somewhere safe,

149
20:16:44,925 --> 20:16:46,158
just to be sure.

150
20:16:46,683 --> 20:16:49,620
But you can't honestly think
John would ever hurt me?

151
20:17:42,300 --> 20:17:43,989
So where did you go?

152
20:17:44,646 --> 20:17:47,337
Oh, here and there. Got married.

153
20:17:48,012 --> 20:17:49,419
- You got what?
- Married.

154
20:17:49,626 --> 20:17:50,571
Why?

155
20:17:51,300 --> 20:17:53,762
Does it add a tingle of the
illicit to the conversation?

156
20:17:53,882 --> 20:17:58,016
It adds a tingle of
disbelief, is what it does.

157
20:17:58,700 --> 20:18:01,006
- Erm, where did you and...
- Bertrand.

158
20:18:02,019 --> 20:18:03,939
A conference in Sao Paolo.

159
20:18:04,265 --> 20:18:06,755
Oh, he was intensely intellectual.

160
20:18:07,425 --> 20:18:09,932
- He "was"?
- Sadly, he passed away.

161
20:18:10,052 --> 20:18:12,854
Some little girls grow up wanting ponies.

162
20:18:14,231 --> 20:18:15,864
I always wanted to be a widow.

163
20:18:18,579 --> 20:18:20,769
So, what about you?

164
20:18:21,740 --> 20:18:25,336
Have you found someone, hmm?

165
20:18:30,100 --> 20:18:31,292
Yeah. Kind of.

166
20:18:32,244 --> 20:18:33,677
And is she interesting?

167
20:18:33,797 --> 20:18:35,291
- To whom?
- Me!

168
20:18:35,660 --> 20:18:37,356
- I don't know.
- Well,

169
20:18:37,476 --> 20:18:39,351
I imagine she wouldn't be, terribly.

170
20:18:39,389 --> 20:18:41,760
She wouldn't be some kind of Zoe surrogate.

171
20:18:42,023 --> 20:18:45,060
You've got enough self-knowledge
to avoid that trap.

172
20:18:49,062 --> 20:18:50,900
So she's a pixie.

173
20:18:51,465 --> 20:18:53,204
- A what?
- A pixie.

174
20:18:54,049 --> 20:18:55,139
A sprite.

175
20:18:55,140 --> 20:18:58,291
A daydream of the life you
imagine you want to live.

176
20:18:59,230 --> 20:19:01,414
Oh, dear, I feel a bit sorry for her.

177
20:19:01,457 --> 20:19:02,746
You don't feel sorry for anyone.

178
20:19:02,803 --> 20:19:03,973
Well, quite.

179
20:19:04,342 --> 20:19:05,937
But in principle, I pity her.

180
20:19:05,962 --> 20:19:08,152
She's not what you want.

181
20:19:08,897 --> 20:19:10,260
She's what you want to want.

182
20:19:10,267 --> 20:19:12,220
What is it I want exactly?

183
20:19:15,535 --> 20:19:17,324
We're not talking about that.

184
20:19:17,731 --> 20:19:19,095
We're talking about Pixie.

185
20:19:19,139 --> 20:19:21,179
- Pix... her name is Mary.
- I know.

186
20:19:30,860 --> 20:19:33,940
'The officer shot dead
last night has been named

187
20:19:34,060 --> 20:19:36,501
'as Detective Sergeant Justin Ripley.

188
20:19:36,500 --> 20:19:39,367
'Detective Sergeant Ripley is
believed to have been killed

189
20:19:39,380 --> 20:19:43,810
'by Tom Marwood who first appealed to
the public in this video yesterday.'

190
20:19:44,592 --> 20:19:45,887
'Four years ago,

191
20:19:46,007 --> 20:19:48,927
'she was raped and murdered
by a man called Milan Knizac.'

192
20:19:49,328 --> 20:19:50,817
This him?

193
20:19:51,380 --> 20:19:52,624
This is him.

194
20:19:53,260 --> 20:19:57,723
Goodness gracious me.
What a needy little fishy.

195
20:19:57,754 --> 20:19:59,712
Oh, he's got a hero complex.

196
20:20:00,457 --> 20:20:03,691
He needs public opinion to
justify his own actions to himself.

197
20:20:07,140 --> 20:20:09,691
So what's the plan, Stan?

198
20:20:10,980 --> 20:20:13,139
I take away everything he wants.

199
20:20:13,140 --> 20:20:14,115
What does he want?

200
20:20:14,121 --> 20:20:15,560
To avenge his wife.

201
20:20:15,680 --> 20:20:17,862
To be admired. To become a martyr.

202
20:20:17,900 --> 20:20:20,227
All to make his wife's
death mean something.

203
20:20:20,684 --> 20:20:22,500
You'd take all that from him?

204
20:20:25,980 --> 20:20:26,853
Yeah.

205
20:20:27,460 --> 20:20:29,060
That's cruel.

206
20:20:30,540 --> 20:20:32,314
It's the cruellest thing I can think of.

207
20:20:34,940 --> 20:20:35,924
Ok.

208
20:20:36,818 --> 20:20:38,627
But if any police

209
20:20:38,747 --> 20:20:40,040
aren't out there looking for him,

210
20:20:40,078 --> 20:20:41,961
they're out there looking for you. So...

211
20:20:43,482 --> 20:20:45,409
how do we even begin?

212
20:20:45,529 --> 20:20:46,479
Well.

213
20:20:47,160 --> 20:20:48,737
First step.

214
20:20:48,931 --> 20:20:50,539
You're Thomas Marwood.

215
20:20:50,552 --> 20:20:52,253
You want to kill the man
that killed your wife.

216
20:20:52,373 --> 20:20:54,737
But Milan Knizac is in prison.

217
20:20:54,793 --> 20:20:57,646
So how would you do it?

218
20:20:59,060 --> 20:21:00,374
With leverage.

219
20:21:01,507 --> 20:21:03,077
Give me a lever long enough

220
20:21:03,390 --> 20:21:05,305
and a fulcrum on which to place it,

221
20:21:05,425 --> 20:21:06,462
and...

222
20:21:08,127 --> 20:21:10,072
I can move the world.

223
20:21:38,740 --> 20:21:39,868
Nat?

224
20:21:46,038 --> 20:21:47,326
Nat?!

225
20:21:57,260 --> 20:21:57,815
Hello?

226
20:21:57,853 --> 20:21:59,160
It's not an easy thing, is it,

227
20:21:59,185 --> 20:22:01,156
when your wife is taken from you?

228
20:22:01,638 --> 20:22:03,445
Well, do as I tell you

229
20:22:03,996 --> 20:22:05,366
and you'll get her back.

230
20:22:34,060 --> 20:22:36,020
What is this place?

231
20:22:38,406 --> 20:22:40,177
Nobody knows we're here, Mary.

232
20:22:40,471 --> 20:22:41,835
Not John,

233
20:22:41,955 --> 20:22:42,936
none of his friends.

234
20:22:42,949 --> 20:22:44,957
So, as long as we stay here,

235
20:22:45,201 --> 20:22:46,546
we're safe, ok?

236
20:22:46,765 --> 20:22:50,020
Just... try and make yourself comfortable.

237
20:23:24,580 --> 20:23:25,846
Benny.

238
20:23:31,820 --> 20:23:33,060
Schenk.

239
20:23:43,780 --> 20:23:45,335
Well, never let it be said

240
20:23:45,373 --> 20:23:48,540
that you are less than
audacious, Miss Morgan.

241
20:23:48,576 --> 20:23:52,048
Well, I've got an issue
with impulse control, Martin.

242
20:23:52,168 --> 20:23:54,545
It's in the genes apparently.

243
20:23:54,607 --> 20:23:58,223
You know, Miss Morgan, I must
remind you, I'm a police officer

244
20:23:58,448 --> 20:24:01,570
and you are a fugitive from justice.

245
20:24:01,620 --> 20:24:03,054
And that, by walking in here,

246
20:24:03,073 --> 20:24:06,595
you have, by default,
surrendered your liberty.

247
20:24:07,083 --> 20:24:09,692
Well, you're entitled to send me back.

248
20:24:10,124 --> 20:24:11,462
I wouldn't take it personally.

249
20:24:11,462 --> 20:24:13,671
- Besides, I'd only escape.
- I have no doubt.

250
20:24:13,677 --> 20:24:15,328
Meanwhile, John will be in prison.

251
20:24:15,541 --> 20:24:16,379
Or dead

252
20:24:17,174 --> 20:24:18,807
at the hands of Tom Marwood.

253
20:24:21,234 --> 20:24:23,617
Now, me, I'm as guilty as sin.

254
20:24:24,043 --> 20:24:25,732
Name it, I've done it.

255
20:24:25,769 --> 20:24:26,551
But...

256
20:24:26,952 --> 20:24:30,474
John's as innocent as I am culpable.

257
20:24:30,912 --> 20:24:34,171
So I suppose the question I'm
here to ask is which matters more?

258
20:24:34,653 --> 20:24:36,205
Punishing my guilt?

259
20:24:36,981 --> 20:24:38,977
Or proving John's innocence?

260
20:24:39,700 --> 20:24:40,728
Now John

261
20:24:41,404 --> 20:24:43,843
has asked me to tell you that Tom Marwood

262
20:24:43,963 --> 20:24:46,609
won't allow himself to be arrested.

263
20:24:47,500 --> 20:24:49,924
He intends to commit suicide by cop,

264
20:24:49,955 --> 20:24:51,926
to die a martyr to his own cause.

265
20:24:52,046 --> 20:24:54,792
Now John knows how to bring him in alive.

266
20:24:54,836 --> 20:24:55,887
But...

267
20:24:56,644 --> 20:24:58,302
he's going to need

268
20:24:59,053 --> 20:25:00,210
your support.

269
20:25:01,780 --> 20:25:03,780
What exactly does he need?

